trend_summary: Throughout the sequence, the area remains predominantly rural. Central woodland persists, but peripheral tree cover is incrementally cleared, enlarging pastures and cropland. A handful of new farm buildings and access tracks emerge, yet no clustered urban growth appears. Land use therefore shifts toward slightly intensified agriculture without altering overall low-density character.
notable_changes: Progressive clearing of forest edges, especially in the southwest and east, expanding pastureland.
Appearance of several small farm structures and sheds near existing roads.
Minor extension and straightening of unpaved access tracks connecting fields.
Agricultural plots become more regular and consolidated over time.
Core forest block remains largely intact despite edge retreat.
